title: Hear why Billie Eilish sees Jimmy Fallon as a brown rectangle
description: Singer Billie Eilish talked about living with a condition called synesthesia on "The Tonight Show" and explained why it makes her perceive Jimmy Fallon as a brown rectangle.

title: Why Trump can't resist running in 2024
description: Sean Spicer says former President Donald Trump will run for president in 2024. Although the former White House press secretary has a well-earned reputation for spreading misleading information, I agree with him on this point. However, I part company with Spicer when he explains why he's certain Trump is "in." He sees evidence in former President's confabs with key advisers. But me? I see it in the merch.

title: A new 'Batman' comic confirms that sidekick Robin is queer
description: The latest issue of a Batman comic series confirms the Caped Crusader's lovable sidekick, Robin, is queer.

title: Congressman walks out interview when asked about his vaccination status
description: U.S. Congressman Glenn Grothman from Wisconsin was asked whether or not he has been vaccinated for Covid-19. See his reaction.

title: 'Childhood memories are burned': Residents in Greece describe devastation
description: Greece is facing a "natural disaster of unprecedented proportions," according to Greek Prime Minister, Kyriakos Mitsotakis. People across dozens of villages were forced to evacuate, as firefighters are battling the blazes.

title: Nurse in Mississippi: 'It feels like we're fighting an unwinnable war'
description: Mississippi nurse Nichole Atherton speaks with CNN's Erica Hill about her decision to resign and pleads with unvaccinated individuals to get vaccinated.

title: Europe's highest and most active volcano spews fresh lava
description: Europe's highest and most active volcano, Sicily's Mount Etna, has erupted in the early hours of Monday.

title: Kristen Bell and Dax Shepard defend 'waiting for the stink' comments
description: Dax Shepard and Kristen Bell defend recent comments made about "waiting for the stink" in relation to bathing their children. HLN's Melissa Knowles reports.

title: Residents evacuated after their Miami condo building deemed unsafe
description: Residents of an eight-story Miami condo housing 138 units were evacuated overnight after their building was deemed unsafe. Buildings in the Miami area have come under increased scrutiny since June 24, when a huge portion of Champlain Towers South crumbled to the ground in Surfside, killing 98 people.

title: From Cold War relics to hot-selling souvenirs of peace: Maestro Wu's Kinmen Knives
description: In the three decades after China's civil war ended in 1949, the residents of Kinmen lived under constant fear.

title: Robert Durst testifies in his murder trial
